<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Parliamentary Assembly of Russia-Belarus Union Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The eighth assembly of the parliament
of the Russia-Belarus Union opened Monday in Gomel, Belarus, with
a call for more initiative from members.
</P>
<P>
At the session Russian State Duma speaker Gennady Seleznyov was
re-elected chairman of the parliament of the Union, and Speaker of
the lower house of the Belarussian parliament Anatoly Malofeyev
was elected deputy chairman.
</P>
<P>
Belarus President Alexander Lukashenko said at the session that
preparations for a new bilateral treaty stipulating the Union's
tasks should be completed by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
As chairman of the Supreme Council of the Union, Lukoshenko
highlighted the importance of the parliament, noting the
initiative of members of the parliament had "begun to ebb".
</P>
<P>
"If the integration process dies down, people will lose faith
in the union's development," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries' unity should be restored on a
qualitatively new democratic basis with regard to mutual
interests, national sovereignty, mutual respect and peaceful
co-existence.
</P>
<P>
The Russia-Belarus Union was founded in April 1997 for
promotion of the two countries' economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
