<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania: Government to Support Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The government of Romania must be
involved in supporting export trade-- this is the highlight of a
survey on Romanian export options initiated and financed by
European Union's PHARE program.
</P>
<P>
According to the state news agency of Romania Rompres, the
survey published on Monday remarked that "the Government's
involvement in supporting export trade, exists in most of the
developed or developing countries", and "a Romanian Foreign Trade
Center and a Department for export promoting must be set in place
under the Ministry of Industry and Trade."
</P>
<P>
The survey says that "Romania has to include all the
responsibilities in a sole body, like Hungary does".
</P>
<P>
"Very important in promoting exports is to help people with
more information about the best opportunities for their own
companies", the survey said. To this respect, Romania "has to take
the cue from other countries and those who know how to do
business".
</P>
<P>
As for the financial measures, "the high nominal interest rates
bring about insecurity and affect people's confidence in the
business milieu, this adds to the doubt about the long-term
exchange rate", the same survey pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The subsidized loans for exports seem to cover at the moment
but 10-15 percent of the goods exports, the survey also said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
