<HEADLINE> ASEAN General Secretary Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Visiting General Secretary of ASEAN
(the Association of Southeast Asian Nations) Rodolfo Severino said
here Monday that he was confident that with Vietnam's active
preparations, the upcoming sixth ASEAN summit scheduled for
December in Hanoi will result in success.
</P>
<P>
Severino, who arrived here last weekend for an official visit
to Vietnam, made the remarks during a meeting with Vietnamese
Prime Minister Phan Van Khai Monday.
</P>
<P>
Severino briefed Khai on main points of the "Hanoi Plan of
Action" and other documents to be submitted to the upcoming ASEAN
summit.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Prime Minister hoped that cooperative ties
between Vietnam and ASEAN would be further enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Khai said the Hanoi summit should concretize its plan of action
in line with the spirit of the "ASEAN Vision 2020" approved by
leaders of member countries at the second informal ASEAN summit in
Kuala Lumpur late last year.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader said that ASEAN should find its own
development way to overcome the adverse impacts of the current
financial crisis in the region and continue to achieve high
socio-economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam expressed the hope that cambodia would be considered to
become the tenth member of ASEAN, said the Vietnamese Prime
Minister.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam joined ASEAN, which also groups Brunei, Indonesia,
Malaysia, Myanmar, Laos, the Philippines, Singapore and Thailand,
in july 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
