to assist in increasing per capita income and living standards of
Palestinian small-scale farmers, according to U.N. sources.
</P>
<P>
The loan comes after the International Monetary Fund and the
World Bank paied attention to the Palestinians' poor living
conditions and low per capita income in the Palestinian self-rule
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli policy of closure has made Palestinians' life even
harder and inflicted serious damages to the Palestinian economy.
