<HEADLINE> Chechen President Sent Massage to Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Chechen President Aslan Maskhadov on
Monday sent a massage to Russian President Boris Yeltsin,
expressing regret over the capture of Russian presidential envoy
to Chechnya, the Itar-Tass news agency reported from Grozny.
</P>
<P>
According to Chechen press secretary Mairbek Vachagayev, the
Chechen president in his massage said that the organizers and
perpetrators of the political provocation had the purpose to
complicate relations between Moscow and Grozny and aggravate the
situation in the Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov meanwhile briefed Yeltsin on the measures taken by
the Chechen police to find and release Russian envoy Valentin
Vlasov.
</P>
<P>
He as well expressed hope that the incident will not
complicated the bilateral relations between Russia and Chechnya
and that through joint efforts Chechen and Russian law enforcers
"will detain and keep most severely, no matter where they come
from."
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov assured Yeltsin that he personally controls the
entire operation for finding and freeing Vlasov and will do his
utmost for the speedy liberation of the envoy.
</P>
<P>
Vlasov was kidnapped on May 1 on his way from Grozny to
Nazzran, and his whereabouts is still unknown.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting held Monday with prefects and clergymen in Grozny
the Chechen president urged the public to unite and rebuff the
criminal world. 
</P>
