<HEADLINE> French Communists Call for Strict Control of Lay-offs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The deputies of the French Communist
Party (PCF) in the National Assembly Monday presented a draft law
to fight against social exclusion, in which they urged a strict
control of lay-offs of workers by enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The PCF deputies said that unemployment is the primary cause of
poverty in France and that there can be no efficient fight against
unemployment without a strict control on lay-offs of workers by
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"There can be no lasting fight to lower unemployment rate
without fighting the lay-offs, and in the first place operate a
strict control on the lay-offs," they said.
</P>
<P>
France's unemployment rate now stands at 12 percent, which
means that around three million people of working age remain
jobless.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly will begin to discuss the draft law from
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The PCF deputies proposed that the government impose more taxes
on those enterprises which make great profits but are laying off
workers.
</P>
<P>
They also proposed that the government subsidize new fund to
help young people look for jobs, provide free transports to the
unemployed, and offer more financial support to build public
residences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
