<HEADLINE> Greece Says Disappointed With Impasse of Cyprus Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Greece Monday voiced its regret and
disappointment with the impasse of the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas described the
conditions raised by Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash during
talks with U.S. presidential emissary for Cyprus, Richard
Holbrooke, as "unacceptable."
</P>
<P>
Denktash reportedly insisted that he would not return to the
negotiating table unless his northern Cyprus was recognized and
the Republic of Cyprus stopped its efforts to join the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
