demilitarization of Cyprus displayed the interest of Moscow in
disarmament and included points which Cyprus President Glafcos
Clerides had put forward in the past.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkish troops occupied
the northern third of the island in the wake of an abortive-coup
backed by Athens.
</P>
<P>
To protest against the EU's decision to include Cyprus in the
list of countries waiting to join the community, northern Cyprus
suspended its talks with Cyprus for the settlement of the
protracted Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
Greece, Cyprus' major supporter, warned in recent days that if
anyone tried to create problems over Cyprus' accession to the EU,
there would be no EU enlargement. 
