<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 4 (Xinhua) -- "La Somme", the Flagship of
the French Naval Forces in the Indian Ocean, arrived Monday at
the Dar es Salaam Port, starting a four-day courtesy call to
Tanzania to cement bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Rear Admiral Stephane LEGRIX de la SALLE, commander of the
French maritime forces in the Indian Ocean, told a press
conference aboard the ship that the visit is aimed at promoting
the friendly cooperation between France and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The Rear Admiral said that his ship with 200 staff will leave
Tanzania for Mozambique and South Africa before returning back to
the northern Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
"Ten Tanzanian Navy officers will begin to be trained aboard
the 'La Somme' for specific courses for about four weeks
according to an agreement between the two navies," said Salle, a
55-year-old Antisubmarine Warfare specialist who has been
selected as a rear admiral since March 1, 1996 and has taken
command of the French maritime forces in the Indian Ocean on
February 21, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The "La Somme", which is also a replenishment ship, remains
anchored at the Dar es Salaam Port throughout her visit while
Rear Admiral Salle and senior French officers will pay a call to
the Zanzibar isles Tuesday by small gun-boats of the Tanzanian
Navy.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Ocean is an essential area for international trade,
especially for the French trade as about 10 French trade ships
sail daily through the Ocean toward the southern islands, eastern
Africa or southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
France maintains old and strong historical, cultural and
defense ties with the whole area. It is also linked to a dozen of
neighboring states through defense or military cooperation
agreements.
</P>
<P>
The command of the naval operation in the Indian Ocean is
under the authority of the Chief of Staff of the French armed
forces and is shared among two zones, the northern zone and the
southern one.
</P>
<P>
the French Naval Forces in the Indian Ocean (the Northern
Zone), commanded by Rear Admiralque Salle, consists of a dozen of
frigates, submarines, patrol boats and supply ships. 
</P>
