<HEADLINE> Number of AIDS Victims Keeps Growing in Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of AIDS victims keeps
growing in the Republic of Moldova, the Moldovan news agency
INTERLIK reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
During the first four months of this year, 167 AIDS infection
cases have been registered at 24 administrative regions of the
Republic, which is two times more than that in the corresponding
period of last year, according to Stefan Georgita, the head of the
National Center for AIDS prevention and control.
</P>
<P>
The number of people infected with AIDS fluctuates from 32 in
Kishinev, the capital of the Republic, to 132 in Belti
municipality.
</P>
<P>
Stefan Georgita said that in most cases this infection has been
identified among people below 35 years old. Eightyfive percent of
them consume drugs intravenously.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistic data, since the beginning of 1998,
2,723 drug addicts have been registered in the medical
institutions of the country and in the police. However, according
to the World Health organization and the Republican clinic for
drug addicts, the number is about 40,000 people who have become
victims of AIDS.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
