<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Macao Promotion Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Promotion Week featuring
promotions related to the region and the Basic Law of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) was launched today in Beijing
as one of activities to greet the region's return to China on
December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The week started with a photograph and stamp exhibition
carrying the theme Macao Today in the National Museum of Chinese
History.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition featured 99 photographs, 69 pictures related to
Macao's industrial development and foreign trade, 204 pictures and
charts and documents concerning the Basic Law and 126 sets of
stamps issued by the Macao government since 1982.
</P>
<P>
Zong Guangyao, vice-director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao
Branch, said the Macao Promotion Week will enhance the awareness
of people in inland areas concerning the history and status of
Macao, as well as the Basic Law and the policy of "one country,
two systems." The event will also help ensure the smooth
transition of power.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, sponsored by the Macao Association of
China-funded Enterprises and the Macao Daily News, will also be
held in Shanghai, Guangzhou, Shenyang and Chongqing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
