<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Appoints Yuzhanov Land Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Ilya Yuzhanov, 38, has been appointed
as Russia's Minister for Land Policies, Construction and
Utilities, the Itar-Tass news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The appointment, made by Russian President Boris Yeltsin
followed a meeting with Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko,
presidential press secretary Sergei Yastrzhembsky said.
</P>
<P>
Yuzhanov, who graduated from the Lenigradsky State University,
had been the chairman of the State Committee for Agrarian Reform
and Land Resources since May 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Vladimir Kuramin was dismissed from the post of the
chairman of the State Committee for the Country's Northern Regions
owing to his retirement.
</P>
<P>
Viktor Bishkaryov was dismissed as the head of the State
Committee for State Reserves.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday was the third time Yeltsin and Kiriyenko had announced
new members of the reshuffled government.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of cabinet members, including two deputy prime
ministers, were appointed on April 28. And the second, including a
deputy prime minister and 10 ministers, were appointed on April
30.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin and Kiriyenko will meet again Friday, said the
Itar-Tass report. 
</P>
