<HEADLINE> IBM Implementing New Strategy in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- IBM signed memorandums with some
China's independent software providers here today, to jointly
provide Electronic-Business solutions for China's small and
medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
For the enterprises IBM has introduced a new generation of
Intel-based servers called Netfinity that will provide a platform
for Electronic-Business.
</P>
<P>
IBM's cooperation with Chinese partners is expected to
provide Chinese clients using Netfinity with solutions applied
to financial, stocks, manufacturing, broadcasting, TV, press and
publishing areas, as well as with softwares involving personnel,
financial, and information management.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation is believed to be crucial to IBM in increasing
its share of China's information technology markets. And IBM is
shifting its investment focus in China to the country's small and
medium-sized businesses.
</P>
<P>
China now has more than 10 million small and medium-sized
enterprises, which contribute 60 percent of the nation's GDP. The
enterprises grow at more than 20 percent a year in terms of
production. 
