<HEADLINE> New Efforts Being Made for Switzerland to Join </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A group of Swiss politicians and
experts are trying to launch an initiative to hold a nationwide
vote on the issue if Switzerland should be a member of the United
Nations after Swiss voters rejected UN membership in a referendum
in 1986, according to a news report by the Swiss Radio
International on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The group believes that the UN is the only international
organization which can play a role in solving conflicts
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The group said that there was little understanding abroad for
Switzerland's position, since the country is already paying
contributions to the organization.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is not a UN member but the United Nations Office at
Geneva (UNOG) and dozens of other UN agencies and international
organizations like the World Health Organization (WHO), the
International Telecommunications Union (ITU) and the World Trade
Organization (WTO) are based in the western Swiss city of Geneva.
</P>
</TEXT>
