<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1630 GMT, May 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Court of Justice has rejected
Britain's challenge to the legality of the European Commission ban
on British beef exports.
</P>
<P>
The court stressed that the commission, the executive body of
the 15-nation European Union, had acted in the interests of public
health.
</P>
<P>
But Britain argued that the commission had exceeded its power
in imposing the ban in March 1996 after London admitted a link
between "mad cow disease" and its human variation,
Creutzfeld-Jacob Disease (CJD). (EU-Britain-Madcow Disease)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said
Tuesday that he was hopeful the London peace talks could achieve
some progress in restoring the flagging Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said after a 75-minute meeting with British Prime
Minister Tony Blair early Tuesday that Israel was working to move
the process forward.
</P>
<P>
"We are working on it. We are working to move the process
forward and if everyone is committed to that, we can do it,"
Netanyahu said. (UK-Netanyahu-Blair)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodia's Second Prime Minister Hun Sen and
deposed First Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh reached a
conciliation Thursday on the election procedure dispute, thus
avoiding a National Assembly (parliament) crisis.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen told the reporters after an assembly session that he
had called Ranariddh Tuesday, asking him to send assembly members
to attend the parliamentary session for the amendment to the
Election Law. (Cambodia-Assembly Crisis)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM -- Seventy Tanzanian passengers have got drowned
while 25 others were hurt when their bus was swept away by floods,
Dar es Salaam newspapers reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bus accident happened Sunday afternoon when the driver
risked crossing a bridge at Kibanda, two kilometers from Muheza
Town, Tanga Region.
</P>
<P>
The overloaded bus, with a capacity of 65 seats, however, was
washed off the bridge by flash floods and fell into the river.
(Tanzania-accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- Ethiopians celebrated Tuesday celebrated
Patriots Victory Day Marking the Ethiopians defeated the Italian
invaders in 1941.
</P>
<P>
In Addis Ababa, the victory day was colourfully celebrated in
the presence of Addis Ababa's Chief Administrator, Ali Abdo,
President of the Ethiopian Patriots Association Asefa Bayou,
veterans and thousands of residents at the Miazia 27 Square. Ali
Abdo laid a wreath under the Victory Monument at the square.
(Ethiopia-Patriots Victory Day) 
