<HEADLINE> Chinese, Spanish Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said today that Sino-Spanish ties enjoy broad prospects
thanks to the joint efforts of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark during a meeting with his Spanish
counterpart Abel Matutes y Juan. He said that China and Spain have
enjoyed the smooth development of cooperation in various fields
since the two nations forged diplomatic ties 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Frequent exchange visits between senior leaders of the two
countries has been and will continue to be of great significance
in improving mutual understanding and the in-depth development of
bilateral ties, said Tang.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed to expanded cooperation in fields of the
economy and trade, science and technology, and culture and
education.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed gratitude for the Spanish government's strict
adherence to a friendly policy towards China and its contributions
to the advancement of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government places high value for all
aspects of friendly cooperation with Spain.
</P>
<P>
China and Spain are important countries in their respective
regions, said Tang, adding that Sino-Spanish relations are an
important component of Sino-European ties.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to further improve Sino-European relations by
further developing Sino-Spanish ties and will extend great efforts to
establish a long-term, stable and constructive partnership between
Chin and Europe, said Tang.
</P>
<P>
Matutes said that Spain and China enjoy sound political ties,
and noted that his country regards developing ties with China as
one of its foreign policy priorities.
</P>
<P>
Spain upholds the "one China" policy and maintains a
constructive attitude on the human rights issue, according to
Matutes.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the enormous potential for bilateral economic and
trade ties, and said his government will encourage Spanish
enterprises to invest in China and further expand exchanges
and cooperation with the country.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers exchanged views and reached a consensus
on the integrity of European currencies, Asian-European
cooperation and the financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Matutes arrived here this morning to begin an official visit at
the invitation of Tang.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish delegation will also visit Shanghai, China's
largest commercial center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
