<HEADLINE> HKMC Lays Foundation for Sound Mortgage Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Mortgage Corporation
(HKMC) purchased or undertook to purchase 3.2 billion HK dollar
(410 million U.S. dollars) floating rate mortgages by the end of
March this year.
</P>
<P>
According to a 1997 annual report published by the HKMC here
Tuesday, the HKMC also launched a pilot scheme for promoting fixed
rate mortgages on March 18 this year.
</P>
<P>
On the funding side, the report said that the HKMC signed an
agreement with the Hong Kong Monetary Authority to appoint the
latter as the arranger, custodian, agent and operator of a 20
billion HK dollar (2.56 billion U.S. dollars) HKMC Note Issuance
Program on 6 January 1998.
</P>
<P>
Two issues had been launched so far which were very well
received by the market, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Donald Tsang, chairman of the Board of Directors of the HKMC,
said in the report that the incorporation of the HKMC in March
last year marked an important milestone in the development of the
residential mortgage market in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
As a pioneer institution, the HKMC provides an important piece
of market infrastructure to kick-start and promote the development
of a secondary mortgage market in Hong Kong, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The Board and the Management of the HKMC look forward to
working closely with the banking community and the capital market
participants to develop a healthy and robust secondary mortgage
market in Hong Kong," he said. 
</P>
