<HEADLINE> Well-Known Macao-Born Portuguese Welcomes Macao SARPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A well-known Portuguese descendent
born in Macao congratulated the formation of the Macao Special
Administrative Region Preparatory Committee (SARPC) Tuesday in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Joaquim Carvalho, 45, chairman of the Islands Municipal
Council, told Xinhua Tuesday that the establishment of the SARPC
means the accomplishment of a historic task in Macao, and that he
was delighted at it.
</P>
<P>
"I'm happy to see that the interests of different community
groups and aspects in Macao have been taken into consideration at
the SARPC," he said. "The working procedure of the SARPC clearly
shows that the Chinese government pays special attention to the
Macao Basic Law and the policy of 'Macao people administering
Macao.'"
</P>
<P>
There are several Macao-born Portuguese (MBP) residents at the
SARPC. They include Leonel Alberto Alves, a certified lawyer, and
Raimundo Rosario, an engineer.
</P>
<P>
Born in Macao, Carvalho speaks good Cantonese and Putonghua
(spoken Chinese) as well as Portuguese. He was vice-chairman of
the Macao Municipal Council before he was appointed to the current
post.
</P>
<P>
Carvalho said the presence of MBP members at the committee
demonstrates that China respects the history of Macao and takes
care of the interests of the MBP residents.
</P>
<P>
In his opinion, the MBP residents are and will continue to be
an important community in Macao. He said it is his hope that the
MBP members will work for Macao's future and represent the
interests of MBP residents.
</P>
<P>
Carvalho said that he was delighted and has "full confidence"
as the Chinese government has reiterated the SARPC will not be a
second power center in Macao, thus avoiding interference in the
Portuguese administration in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
