<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 More AIDS Cases Diagnosed in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen AIDS cases were diagnosed
 in the first quarter of the year, bringing the total number of
such cases to 322 in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Health said here Tuesday that the total
number of reported HIV infection cases in Hong Kong has exceeded
1,000.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter this year, a total of 48 persons were
found to be positive for the HIV antibody test, bringing the cumulative
number of reported HIV infection cases to 1,005.
</P>
<P>
For this quarter, the department said that the ratio of
reported male to female HIV infections is 4 to 1 while that of
heterosexual to homo-sexual HIV infections is 5 to 1.
</P>
<P>
Of all AIDS cases reported, 149 persons had died as of the end
of 1997. The number of deaths in 1995, 1996 and 1997 was 30, 23
and 21 respectively.
</P>
<P>
In Hong Kong, the first case of AIDS was reported in 1985.
</P>
</TEXT>
