There were 65 gainers, 38 losers while the share prices of 62
companies remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100Index closed higher Tuesday as the stock market
staged a minor recovery on punters covering positions prior to a
two-day holiday starting on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that while there was foreign selling in major
scrips which affected the overall sentiment, later in the day
covering by local houses allowed the index to close higher.
