<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Celebrate Patriots Victory Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopians celebrated Tuesday
celebrated Patriots Victory Day Marking the Ethiopians defeated the
Italian invaders in 1941.
</P>
<P>
In Addis Ababa, the victory day was colourfully celebrated in
the presence of Addis Ababa 's Chief Administrator, Ali Abdo,
President of the Ethiopian Patriots Association Asefa Bayou,
veterans and thousands of residents at the Miazia 27 Square. Ali
Abdo laid a wreath under the Victory Monument at the square.
</P>
<P>
Asefa said the victory won by the ill-armed and inefficiently
provisioned gallant patriots against Italian aggressors is a
pride not only to the Ethiopians, but also to all the peoples of
Africa.
</P>
<P>
This is the 57th anniversary of the victory over the
Italian invaders.
</P>
<P>
On May 5, 1941, Emperor Haile Selassie I and patriots entered
the capital, Addis Ababa and raised the national flag. 
</P>
