<HEADLINE> Poll Shows Chirac's Approval Ratings Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac's
political popularity has improved over the past year, according
to a poll by the SOFRES polling institution published Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
38 percent of the people polled said they approved of Chirac's
performance, as compared with 27 percent the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 47 percent said they disapproved, compared with 64
percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Most people think that Chirac has done a good job on diplomacy,
economy, defense, running the government, environmental
protection, European construction, the mass media, and protection
of the French franc.
</P>
<P>
But he was criticized by a majority of people for doing poorly
in the fight against unemployment, raising purchasing power,
reducing social inequality and immigration.
</P>
<P>
The poll was conducted among 1,000 people over 18 from April
21 to 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
