<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Founding of Macao Prep Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- An editorial to be published in the
People's Daily Wednesday hails the setting up of the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) today.
</P>
<P>
Now that the Preparatory Committee has been founded, the work
to establish the Macao SAR has been ushered into a new stage, the
editorial states.
</P>
<P>
"The 100 Preparatory Committee members from Macao and the
inland areas (of the motherland) will exercise the sacred
responsibilities endowed by the National People's Congress (NPC)
and its Standing Committee. The pace of Macao's steady transfer
and smooth return will be faster," the editorial states.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been China's territory since ancient times, but was
taken by Portugal in the middle of the 16th century. Through
negotiations, the two countries sealed an agreement that China
would resume sovereignty over Macao on Dec. 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
On March 31, 1993, the First Session of the Eighth NPC passed
the Basic Law of Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR), which
fixed the fundamental principles concerning Macao's return to the
motherland in the form of law, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
The 60 Preparatory Committee members from Macao extensively
represent the people of various social sectors in Macao, and the
40 members from China's interior areas come from departments
related to Macao affairs and scholars on Macao studies.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see that many questions during the transfer
period of Macao have scored progress through friendly cooperation
and joint efforts between China and Portugal," the editorial
states. "But some key questions which have close links with the
transfer of power of Macao have to be addressed faster."
</P>
<P>
The editorial notes that the two sides should strengthen
cooperation and consultation in the coming 20 months to resolve
remaining questions.
</P>
<P>
Under the strong leadership of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, Macao's
smooth return will surely be a success on the basis of broad
participation of compatriots in Macao and the active support of
people in the interior areas, the experience of Hong Kong's return
and friendly cooperation between China and Portugal, the editorial
states.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
