<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Launches Securities-trading Service System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A new service system with the China
Construction Bank (CCB), one of the nation's four biggest
commercial banks, will allow securities investors to trade through
a current banking account.
</P>
<P>
The bank's Guangzhou branch recently took the lead in starting
the system, which eliminates the need for investors to open
stock-trading accounts with securities companies.
</P>
<P>
The system, co-developed by the CCB Guangzhou branch and the
Guangzhou-based Southern Securities Co. Ltd., now covers all CCB
subsidiaries in the city.
</P>
<P>
The securities investors need to open a current deposit account
with the city's CCB branch and apply for the securities-trading
service. They also need to sign an agreement with the securities
company to authorize the company to be their trading agent.
</P>
<P>
With the current deposit account, investors can check their
balance and their securities equity as well as their trading
record of stocks, funds and state treasury bonds. The dividends
of their stock equity will be automatically deposited into their
account.
</P>
<P>
The investors can also receive a number of other services with
the new account. They may deposit and withdraw cash at any of the
300 banking outlets in Guangzhou, get a credit card and use it in
more than 500 designated shops, and entrust the bank to pay
utilities fees on their behalf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
