<HEADLINE> China to Celebrate 20th Anniversary of Significant CPC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- China will organize a series of
activities this year to mark the 20th anniversary of a significant
meeting of the Communist Party of China (CPC), according to a
circular of the CPC Central Committee which was made public today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the Third Plenary Session of the 11th CPC Central
Committee, which was held on December 18, 1978, made policy
decisions on China's reform and opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The main theme of the celebrations will center on reviewing the
achievements and experience of China's socialist reform and
modernization drive since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central
Committee. Related celebrations will provide the whole Party and
all Chinese people with a deeper understanding of Deng Xiaoping
Theory and the Party's basic line, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the celebrations will be a grand celebration
ceremony in the Great Hall of the People on December 18. General
Secretary of the CPC Central Committee Jiang Zemin will deliver a
keynote speech at the ceremony to be held by the CPC Central
Committee. 
