<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A major fire swept through Beijing's
Yuquanying Furniture Center, the largest venture of its kind in
the Chinese Capital, at around 18:00 pm this evening.
</P>
<P>
Heavy black smoke could been seen as far away as Tian'anmen
Square which in some 10 km distant in the center of the city. The
furniture center is located in the southwestern Fengtai District.
</P>
<P>
So far, no casualties have been reported, according to a
district official. The official noted that the fire is under
control and officials from the concerned departments are currently
investigating the cause.
</P>
<P>
The local public security department confirmed the fire, but
reclined to disclose details.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the Beijing Fengtai Hospital indicate that there
have been no calls for assistance. And a large number of
fire-fighters, police officers and government officials responded
to the site.
</P>
<P>
Residents in nearby neighborhoods report the steady scream of
sirens from emergency vehicles responding to the fire.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is still under investigation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
