<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee for Macao SAR Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee for the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) was established here
today.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), attended the inaugural meeting and
granted certificates of appointment to all members of the
Preparatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li first expressed congratulations to the 100 members of
the Preparatory Committee, then announced the formal establishment
of the Preparatory Committee for the Macao SAR, which was met with
extended warm applause.
</P>
<P>
Of the Preparatory Committee's 100 members, 60 are from
Macao. Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen serves as the chairman of
the Preparatory Committee. Nine persons, including Ma Man Kei and
Xie Fei, serve as vice-chairmen of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that the name list for the committee was put
forward after thorough consultations, which should provide a wide
range of representation in the interests of Macao people.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that, as an institution of authority empowered
by the NPC, the Preparatory Committee will mainly make
preparations for the first government, legislative council and
judiciary of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
The committee will pave the way for China's resumption of
sovereignty over Macao, while laying a solid foundation for the
implementation of the "one country, two systems" principle and
China's reunification cause, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the firm belief that the Macao SAR will be
established as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the NPC,
presided over the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
