<HEADLINE> HK Launches First Broadband Internet Service on iTV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Telecom IMS announced on
Tuesday that a new Internet application will be added to its
multimedia Interactive TV (iTV) services.
</P>
<P>
The Supernetvigator, a broadband Internet service for users in
Hong Kong, will offer remarkably enhanced Internet access speed
and connecting ability via the broadband network.
</P>
<P>
The service speed is up to 1.5 Mbps, 30 times higher than that
of a dial-up connection.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong launched in March the world's first iTV services with
which over 90 percent of local households will be able to see
films, listen to music, shop for fun or deal with individual
financial affairs with clicks on a few remote control buttons at
the comfort of their own homes.
</P>
<P>
Using the PC as the medium, Supernetvigator is supported by two
existing IMS services - iTV and a web service, Netvigator.
</P>
<P>
William Lo, managing director of Hong Kong Telecom IMS, said
the company is "committed to developing a dynamic and
comprehensive range of multimedia services to enhance the way
people live and work."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Telecom IMS, a cable and wireless company, is the
largest Internet service provider in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
