<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Launches Annual Economic Survey Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Census and Statistics
Department of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
government has launched an annual economic survey program.
</P>
<P>
The five surveys included in the program aim at obtaining
up-to-date statistical data for evaluating the relevant economic
activities' contribution to Hong Kong's Gross Domestic Product and
for ascertaining their cost structure, operating characteristics
and output levels.
</P>
<P>
The program kicked off on Monday includes the Annual Survey of
Industrial Production; the Annual Survey of Building, Construction
and Real Estate Sectors; the Annual Survey of Wholesale, Retail
and Import and Export Trades, Restaurants and Hotels; the Annual
Survey of Transport and Related Services; and the Annual Survey of
 Storage, Communication, Financing, Insurance and Business
Services.
</P>
<P>
The survey results are expected to benefit both the government
and the private sector in formulating policies and making
decisions.
</P>
<P>
The Commissioner for Census and Statistics, Frederick Ho,
appealed to the management of all the 23,700 establishments
selected to be enumerated in the program to return the completed
questionnaires and co-operate with officers of the department in
the course of the surveys.
</P>
<P>
In general, information to be sought in the surveys include
type of ownership, affiliation with companies located outside Hong
Kong SAR, floor area, employment, compensation of employees
(i.e. wages, salaries and other employee benefits), operating
expenses, business receipts, capital expenditure and other related
information on the business operation of the establishments.
</P>
<P>
The selected establishments are required by law to complete and
return to the Census and Statistics Department by July 31 this
year the questionnaires of the surveys, which are conducted under
the Census and Statistics Ordinance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
