<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Seventy Tanzanian passengers
have got drowned while 25 others were hurt when their bus was
swept away by floods, Dar es Salaam newspapers reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bus accident happened Sunday afternoon when the driver
risked crossing a bridge at Kibanda, two kilometers from Muheza
Town, Tanga Region.
</P>
<P>
The overloaded bus, with a capacity of 65 seats, however, was
washed off the bridge by flash floods and fell into the river.
</P>
<P>
The driver, who is among the survivors, has been held by the
police.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye inspected the site
soon after the accident. He said the accident could have been
avoided.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Benjamin Mkapa has sent condolences to
the bereaved families of the deceased.
</P>
<P>
He said he was shocked at the accident, which happened less
than one month after the Mererani accident, in which more than 90
miners were buried alive at a tanzanite mine in the northern
region of Arusha.  
</P>
