<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Holds First Plenum (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The first plenary meeting of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR) was held today in the Great Hall of the People in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the start of preparatory work for the Macao SAR,
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said the Preparatory Committee
will face a great deal of urgent work and that he hopes the
committee members will make a combined effort for the smooth
transition and transfer of power in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also chairman of the Preparatory Committee, said that
realizing the return of Macao in accordance with the "one country,
two systems" principle is another significant event for the
Chinese nation after Hong Kong's return. It is also the common
aspiration of all Chinese people, including Macao compatriots, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Empowered by the National People's Congress (NPC), the
Preparatory Committee is an institution of power as well as a
working body, and it will be responsible for matters related to
the establishment of the Macao SAR, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee will work out a method of electing
the Chief Executive of the Macao SAR, establish a 200-member
Selection Committee entirely composed of permanent Macao
residents. The Selection Committee will elect a candidate for the
Chief Executive and submit the nomination to the central
government for appointment, Qian explained.
</P>
<P>
Besides, he said, the members of the Preparatory Committee will
formulate procedures on forming the first legislature and
judiciary of the Macao SAR, and procedures on handling major legal
matters related to the smooth transition. They will also study
questions in connection with the transition in political,
economic, social and cultural areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
