<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to decline
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) fell further by another 7.13 points to close at
1469.27 points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the stocks went lower in the absence of fresh
developments, while foreign institutional investors stayed away,
wary of the region's economic and financial woes.
</P>
<P>
Mild selling interest in some bank shares and property issues
arose late in the afternoon, they added.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased marginally to 109.19 million
units, valued at 195.3 million Singapore dollars (about 123.61
million U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 231 to 68,
while 293 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Easyknit was again the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 20.97 million units. It was followed by
M. Resources which had 5.48 million shares traded. Rekapac was
next with 4.84 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by one dollar to finish at 31.5 Singapore
dollars. Shangri la increased by 13 cents to end at 2.65 Singapore
dollars, while local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) was up
by ten cents to close at 6.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life was the biggest loser as it declined
by 80 cents to end at 12.2 Singapore dollars. Transmarco fell by
70 cents to close at 6.2 Singapore dollars. Asean and DBS
(Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign lost 50 cents each to
finish at eight U.S. dollars and ten Singapore dollars
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
