<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman to Visit Four Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), will pay an official goodwill visit to
Romania, Italy, Spain and France from May 14 to 30.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here this afternoon by Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao at a routine press conference.
</P>
<P>
Li is invited by President of the Romanian Senate Peter Roman,
President of the Italian Chamber of Deputies Luciano Violante,
President of the Spanish Senate Juan Ignacio Barrero, and
President of the French Senate Rene Monory, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said this is CPPCC Chairman's first visit to the four
countries, during which Li will exchange views with leaders of the
four countries on furthering bilateral relations and other issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
This visit is expected to promote understanding, expand common
ground, further friendship and push forward cooperation, as well
as help the further growth of the friendly relations between China
and the four countries, the foreign ministry spokesman said.
</P>
