<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Meets Sri Lankan Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Olaara Otunnu, United Nations
Special Representative of the Secretary General on children and
Armed Conflict who is on a week long visit to Sri Lanka, met
foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
An official news release issued Tuesday afternoon said in his
discussion with kadirgamar, Otunnu pointed out the need to build a
positive political atmosphere in order to provide relief measures
for the victims of war.
</P>
<P>
Otunnu said that concerted post-conflict action must be taken
to address the needs of trauma, rehabilitation and psychological
healing. For this purpose action programs in the field of health,
education and social services were necessary, said the release.
</P>
<P>
Kadirgamar explained to Otunnu that in Sri Lanka children were
affected by the war in many ways. Children have become victims of
the conflict as a result of a father being killed or disabled by
serving in the armed forces or by living in the conflict areas.
</P>
<P>
All children who are subjected to trauma, disabilities in the
war would be the beneficiaries of a national program to be
implemented in Sri Lanka, the release was quoted the minister as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Otunnu appreciated the keenness of the government to have
practical measures in place as soon as possible. He undertook to
work towards obtaining the maximum support for the Sri Lankan
program from the various agencies, organizations and countries
that operate in this area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
