<HEADLINE> China Spokesman Refutes So-Called "Threat" to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao today refuted Indian Defense Minister George
Fernandes' recent remark to the effect that China is India's top
potential threat.
</P>
<P>
Such a remark is ridiculous and fragile, Zhu said at today's
news conference, adding that Fernandes' criticism of China's
relationship with other countries is also groundless fabrication.
</P>
<P>
What the Indian Defense Minister said seriously damaged the
sound environment for developing Sino-Indian relations, and the
Chinese side has to express its deep regret and dissatisfaction,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China has always sought to develop friendly,
cooperative relations with India, Pakistan, and other neighboring
countries under the guidance of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
China does not pose any threat to other countries, and this
principled stance of China is open, aboveboard and also known to
all, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
