<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Tuesday as players were
concerned over the local corporate sector's health and that of
regional economies.
</P>
<P>
In the absence of fresh local positive indicators, the market's
activities were dampened by other regional equity markets and the
local market was further pressured by the selling of bluechips,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index fell 19.03
points to 608.40, the all-share Emas Index eased 4.59 points to
152.86, the Industrial Index was 32.20 points lower at 1,109.77
and the Second Board Index shed 2.68 points to 131.38.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 625 to 77, while 100 were
unchanged and 113 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 127.186 million shares valued
at 314.223 million ringgit (about 85.155 million U.S. dollars)
from 113.452 million shares worth 282.125 million ringgit (about
76.456 million U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover rose to 118.440 million shares valued
at 301.035 million ringgit (about 81.581 million U.S. dollars)
from 106.905 million shares worth 271.675 million ringgit (about
73.624 million U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover was higher at 8.746 million shares
valued at 13.188 million ringgit (about 3.573 million U.S.
dollars) from Monday's 6.547 million shares worth 10.449 million
ringgit (about 2.831 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market volume dipped to 4.200 million shares valued at
13.897 million ringgit (about 3.766 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 4.845 million shares worth 31.252 million ringgit (about
8.469 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 8.131
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
11.593 million shares, construction 9.150 million shares,
trading/service 32.197 million shares, infrastructure 979,000
shares, finance 21.043 million shares, hotels 606,000 shares,
properties 14.882 million shares, plantation 5.247 million shares,
mining 839,400 shares, trusts 168,000 shares, closed/fund 178,000
shares, loans 13.425 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
