<HEADLINE> Intensive Training Prepares LegCo Election in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A mock polling was undergone here
Tuesday afternoon as part of the intense training of the polling
staff for Hong Kong's first Legislative Council Election on May
24.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 polling staff members gathered in the Queen
Elizabeth Stadium and watched the demonstration of the polling
arrangements and whole process in an on-stage polling station.
</P>
<P>
The staff members, including appointed presiding officers,
polling officers and assistants, also practiced locking of ballot
boxes and paid a familiarization visit to the central counting
station.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, 496 polling stations will be open
throughout the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region to about
2.8 million voters on May 24. The polling stations will be set up
two to three days before the election.
</P>
<P>
Special measures will be taken to aid disabled voters in the
polling stations. 
</P>
