<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Sees Growth in Passenger, Cargo Flow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Both passenger and cargo flow via the
Macao International Airport between January and April this year
increased steadily from the same period last year, the Macao Daily
News reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The airport handled more than 680,000 passengers in the first
four months of this year, up 14 percent. Its cargo transport added
up to 16,245 tons, an increase of 39 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Flights coming and leaving the airport also increased. It
recorded 7,716 flights in the first four months, up 33 percent.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in November 1995, the airport has opened a dozen
air routes to China's inland cities, Taiwan, and some southeast
Asian nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
