<HEADLINE> Ayub Khan Continues to Perform Duty as FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Gohar Ayub Khan, who has expressed
his inability to carry on his assignment as foreign minister owing
to his personal reasons, attended his office and performed his
duty as foreign minister Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to sources in the Foreign Ministry, Ayub Khan may
continue to work as foreign minister till he is assigned a new
portfolio.
</P>
<P>
The sources clarified that he has not resigned from the
cabinet, and had only requested re-assignment of his portfolio.
</P>
<P>
The decision on his request is pending, and it is almost
certain that Ayub Khan would work as foreign minister till Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif makes a decision on his request, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Ayub Khan has dispelled the impression that he had to resign
from his office because of differences with the Cabinet on any
issue and said, "I have not resigned from the Cabinet," adding
that he has only asked the prime minister to change his portfolio.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a spokesman for the Prime Minister's Secretariat
said in a press release Tuesday that Prime Minister Sharif, "while
acceding to Ayub Khan's request for allocation of another
portfolio to him, has decided that for the time being he should
continue to function in his present post." 
</P>
</TEXT>
