</P>
<P>
-- According to latest opinion polls, 35 percent of Israelis
would vote for the incumbent Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu if
the general election was held now while 27 percent would vote for
the opposition Labor party leader Ehud Barak. Only 13 percent
would be in favor of Ronni Milo, who decided Sunday to run for
prime minister. 
