changing the boundary in that region," he said, adding that the
Kosovo issue was the most serious problem in the former
Yugoslavia. It was not necessary for the international community
to interfere in Kosovo, but stronger pressure on the authority in
Yugoslavia should be maintained, he added. (Sweden-Croatia-Kosovo)
