<HEADLINE> Shanghai Becoming Export Outlet for Other Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Tongling Metallurgy Group
Company is in the city of Tongling in east China's Anhui Province,
more than 500 km from Shanghai, China's largest foreign trade
center.
</P>
<P>
It used to cost the company a lot of time, money, and manpower
just to send its products to Shanghai, but these days, things are
much easier and more efficient, because the group has established
an export company in Shanghai. Shanghai has done its best to make
itself into an international economic, financial, and trade center
and into an ideal place to export goods from other parts of the
country.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Shanghai Port handled 30.1 billion US dollars worth of
exports and imports for other provinces and cities, accounting for
51.3 percent of the port's total. And the port handled 18 percent
of China's exports and imports last year.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Port now ranks twelfth in the world, with an
annual handling capacity of 2.52 million TEUs. Domestic and
foreign shipping companies have 106 regular container routes,
making Shanghai the only port in the country with routes to all 12
of the world's major shipping areas.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Customs has also established business links to China's
other provinces and cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
