<DOCNO> XIE19980505.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Population Growth Rate to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's population growth rate will
decline by 2.5 percent by 2000, Planning and National Development
Minister George Saitoti has said.
</P>
<P>
The decline in population growth and fertility is being
achieved by changing people's perception on the costs and
benefits of small families, he said Monday.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by Tuesday's East African Standard newspaper as
saying that Kenya has also played its part in internalizing the
International Conference on Population and Development
resolutions by revising its population policy guidelines,
outlining development targets and expanding the time-frame to
2010.
</P>
<P>
Over the period of 1984-93, the total fertility rate fell from
8.1 to 5.4 percent, while contraceptive prevalence almost
doubled, from 17 to 33 percent, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Population growth also fell in the east African country from
3.8 percent between 1969 and 1979 to 3.4 percent from 1979 to
1989.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government will further reinforce the trends in
fertility decline through improving survival for infants,
improving income earning opportunities for women and enhancing
socio-economic development, said Saitoti. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
