<HEADLINE> Stalactic Cave Found in Three Gorges Reservoir Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A 1,850-meter-long stalactic cave
has been found in Fengdu County in the Three Gorges Reservoir area
in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The cave averages four meters in width and 2.5 meters in
height.
</P>
<P>
A big collection of spectacular corals and a crystalized palace
covering an area of 60 square meters have been found inside
the cave, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
Fengdu, commonly known as a "town of ghosts," is one of the
popular tourism spots in the Three Gorges Reservoir area,
attracting some one million tourists a year. 
</P>
