Tuesday that the country's high real interest rates and tough
anti-inflation monetary policy were getting in the way of an
"investment boom" and there was now increased pressure for a
rapid decrease in the bank rate.
</P>
<P>
Sowetan:
</P>
<P>
-- The South African cabinet is to introduce legislation aimed
at addressing the rocketing costs in medical aid which has seen
more people unable to afford a visit to the doctor.  
</P>
</TEXT>
