<DOCNO> XIE19980505.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> But Now They're Faster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- It took the Chinese princess Wen-Cheng
three years to go from Xi'an, the capital of the Tang Dynasty
(618-907), to Tibet's Lhasa to meet her bridegroom Songzain Gambo,
a famous Tibetan king of the 7th century.
</P>
<P>
She'd be delighted to know that the trip can now be done in
three hours by plane because the Tibet Autonomous Region now has
two commercial airports with domestic and international flights to
other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
Before the peaceful liberation of Tibet in 1951, there was only
one automobile there and that was the exclusive property of the
Dalai Lama. It had been put together from parts carried in on the
backs of pack animals and could only be used on the road that ran
from the Potala Palace to the Dalai Lama's summer palace -- a
distance of less than two kilometers.
</P>
<P>
In the early 1950s, the PLA cut through 14 ridges and built a
highway on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, where the average elevation
is 4,500 meters above sea level, giving Tibet its first
highway. Now, the autonomous region has more than 22,000 km of
highways linked to Lhasa, and all counties, and 77 percent of the
villages.
</P>
<P>
The Sichuan-Tibet highway and the Qinghai-Tibet highway have
played an important role in economic and social progress in Tibet,
according to Liu Jichen, director of the autonomous region's
highway bureau. Lhasa now has regular bus service to prefectures
and neighboring provinces that help Buddhists who come to Lhasa on
pilgrimages.
</P>
<P>
And most stores, whether they are on Bargor Street in the
commercial heart of Lhasa or in a small village in the valley,
have a variety of goods from other parts of China or from India
and Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of shops in Lhasa selling fashionable goods are owned
by people from elsewhere who often bring the latest fashions from
coastal cities like Guangzhou, and they can be quite profitable
because transportation is so much more convenient than before, one
shop owner says.
</P>
<P>
However, transportation is still a problem and hampers the
smooth growth of Tibet's economy and social progress, according to
one senior official, so the local government plans to put more
than one billion yuan (120 million US dollars) into the autonomous
region's highway system in the next three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980505.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Air Force Commander Holds Talks With Chief of U.S.Air Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The friendship and cooperation
between Chinese and U.S. Air Forces should be based on mutual
trust, Commander of the Air Force of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), lieutenant general Liu Shunyao, said in
talks here today with visiting Air Force Chief of Staff of the
United States, general Michael Ryan.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that in recent years, Sino-American relations have
developed well and there have been frequent exchanges of
high-level visits between the two countries and armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Air Force takes an active attitude toward developing
relations with its U.S. counterpart, he said, adding that
high-level visits are common occurences between the two air forces
and professional and technical exchanges are also on the rise.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two air forces should not confine their
contact only to high-ranking officers. It is equally important for
officers of various levels, especially middle-ranking officers of
the two air forces to keep contact because they are the future of
the air forces, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Liu expressed his hope that Ryan's visit to China will bring
substantial progress for the relations of the two air forces so
that a long-term and stable relationship between them can be
established.
</P>
<P>
Ryan agreed with Liu and said that it is important that the
friendly cooperation between the two air forces should be based on
mutual trust and reciprocity.
</P>
<P>
The two generals conducted an in-depth discussion on the future
exchanges and cooperation between the two air forces.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Chief of Staff of PLA Air Force Xu Qiliang
briefed the guests on Chinese Air Force.
</P>
<P>
Ryan arrived here on Monday as Liu's guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
