<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Consume 700 Tons of Tea Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Per-capita consumption of tea by
residents in east China's Shanghai City has reached 0.6
kilograms a year, more than double the national average of 0.25 kg.
</P>
<P>
The city consumed more than 700 tons of tea in 1997, according
to the Shanghai Tea Association.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents prefer green, black, oolong and jasmine tea,
which account for 80 percent of Shanghai's total tea consumption.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents like tea because tea is good for health,
according to the association.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai now has more than 4,000 tea shops.  
</P>
