<HEADLINE> Chinese, Seychelles Vice-Presidents Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao,
during a talk with visiting Vice-President James Michel of
Seychelles here today, expressed his thanks for Seychelles'
adherence to the "one China" stance.
</P>
<P>
Hu said China treasures its ties with Seychelles and is ready
to work with the country to advance bilateral relations in a
long-term and stable way.
</P>
<P>
China-Seychelles relations have been growing steadily with a
frequent exchange of high-level visits and effective cooperation
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties 22 years ago, Hu
added.
</P>
<P>
He described bilateral relations as "honest and friendly",
which are based on equality, mutual trust, mutual respect and
mutual support.
</P>
<P>
The economic and trade cooperation between China and Seychelles
has witnessed fruitful result with the expansion of cooperative
fields and forms over the past years, Hu noted, adding that there
is still potential in bilateral economic cooperation which has
broad prospect.
</P>
<P>
Michel said Seychelles-China ties have always been good and
China has provided positive support to Seychelles' economic
development, for which Seychelles is quite grateful.
</P>
<P>
Michel told Hu that Seychelles appreciates China's stance that
all nations should be equal and is willing to advance friendly and
cooperative ties with China in every area.
</P>
<P>
The two vice-presidents also reached consensus on major
regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Hu also voiced his appreciations of Seychelles' political
stability, economic development and the country's role in regional
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Michel said China's experience in economic development is worth
learning and said that his country support China's principle of
"one country, two systems" to reunite the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the issue of Taiwan will
eventually be settled with the successful return of Hong Kong and
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Hu presided over a welcome ceremony in
honor of Michel who is on a visit to China as Hu's guest.  
</P>
