<HEADLINE> Private Enterprise to Offer Railway Cargo Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A special freight train run for the
first time by a private enterprise has gone into operation,
running between Guangzhou and Shenyang via Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The contractor, Liaoning Haicheng Fukui Group and Shenyang
Dingfeng Commerce and Trade Company, takes charge of cargo
organization, loading and unloading, and escorting the 22-car
train.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement with the Ministry of Railways, the
two companies will contract the train for the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The private freight operation is expected to sharpen the
competitive edge of railway transportation in the market by
diversifying managers and encouraging competition, instead of
depending on governmental operation alone, transit experts said.
</P>
<P>
Railway transportation has been challenged by express highways
and air cargo flights in recent years. Statistics show that the
share of railways had decreased from 60.5 percent to 38.8 percent
in transportation volume in the 1980-1995 period.
</P>
<P>
A key to transportation system reform is to build a
market-oriented structure covering different management patterns,
according to Fu Zhihuan, newly appointed Railway Minister.
</P>
<P>
Another source said that three farmers in Liangshan County,
Shandong Province, built China's first private railway line early
this year. The 630-meter line serves a nearby oil depot.
</P>
<P>
"It's OK for whether the State, local government, or
individuals to build or operate railways, so long as the activity
is in accordance with officially approved procedures," said Sima
Ke, an official with the Transport Bureau of the Ministry of
Railways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
