<HEADLINE> Kenyan Armed Forces' Top Echelons Readjusted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Major changes have been made within
the top echelons of the Kenyan Armed Forces, the independent East
African Standard newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
General Daudi Tonje remains the Chief of General Staff but his
deputy will now be Major General Daniel Opande, who has been
promoted to the rank of Lieutenant General, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Before the elevation, Opande was the Commandant of the Kenya
National Defence College. Now he replaces Major General Jack
Munyao who has reportedly retired after attaining the mandatory
age.
</P>
<P>
Opande's place has been taken by Kenya Navy Commander Joseph
Kibwana.
</P>
<P>
Army Commander Lieutenant General Augustine Cheruiyot has been
taken by Major General A. Aden who has also been promoted to
Lieutenant General. Cheruiyot is set to retire on June 8.
</P>
<P>
Aden's deputy will be Major General H.W. Njoroge.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier Rauf Rauf has been promoted to a Major General and
will take Kibwana's place in the Navy.
</P>
<P>
Major General John Koech now becomes the Commandant of the
Defence Staff College.
</P>
<P>
Defense spokesman George Nyakundi was quoted as saying that
the changes took place with effect from May 1.  
</P>
