<HEADLINE> China to Have 1,000,000-KW Wind-Driven Power Facilities by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- China has planned to install
wind-driven power generators with a combined capacity of one
million kilowatts (kw) by 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the China State Power
Corp., the country now has 15 large wind-power generation fields
with a combined capacity of more than 30,000 kw and 10 million
small wind-power generators with a total capacity of 20,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
China now can produce 30,000 wind-driven power generators
annually.
</P>
<P>
The official said China will continue to carry out its policy
of manufacturing small wind-driven power generators for household
usage in border areas and remote regions who are not connected to
national power grids.
</P>
<P>
The country is phasing out a plan to develop wind power in
provinces which are rich in wind resources but lack in power
supplies.
</P>
<P>
The official said that China is abundant in wind resources, and
about two-thirds of the country's land area is windy with total
wind-energy resources estimated at 253 million kw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
