<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Up in April in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' inflation rate
climbed to 7.9 percent in April from 7.3 percent last month on a
year-on-year base, the National Statistics Office (NSO) said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NSO said in a press release that the increase was mainly
due to higher prices of food, beverages and tobacco, housing and
repairs, and clothing as a result of the financial turmoil in
Southeast Asia, including the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
However, the NSO said that fuel, light, water and services
recorded lower prices than expected.
</P>
<P>
By region, the inflation rate for Metro Manila rose to 8.8
percent from 7.6 percent last month, the highest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The average inflation rate during the first four months of the
year was 7.3 percent, 2.2 percentage points higher than last
year's average. 
</P>
