<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen One of World's Leading Toy Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Statistics show that the Shenzhen
Special Economic Zone has become one of the world's leading toy
producers.
</P>
<P>
The variety of toys produced in the world is estimated at
150,000. Shenzhen now turns out about 100,000 varieties.
</P>
<P>
According to authorized figures, the United States last year
imported 10 billion U.S. dollars in toys, with China accounting
for 5.4 billion U.S. dollars. Of China's total, 2.2 billion
U.S. dollars was from Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Most of the toy makers in Shenzhen are receiving funds from
neighboring Hong Kong. At present, there are 840 Hong Kong-funded
toy factories employing 600,000 workers in Shenzhen, making up
one-sixth of China's toy makers.
</P>
<P>
The toy makers in Shenzhen have been constantly improving their
product quality in recent years, officials said. At present, 20
toy factories in Shenzhen have been awarded ISO9000 certification
by the International Standardization Organization.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,000 "creditable enterprises" chosen by Shenzhen
Customs each year, toy factories make up a large proportion. As
high as 98.3 percent of the exported toys from Shenzhen stand up
to qualification standards.
</P>
<P>
The success of the toy industry in Shenzhen is attributable to
timely information provided by Hong Kong investors about world toy
trends and the development of high-tech products, market analysts
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
