<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Mahathir Calls for Mobilization of Wealth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad Tuesday called for the full mobilization of the
people's own wealth to help the country recover from the current
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
The wealth of Malaysians has not been fully mobilized, he said
at the launch of "Asnita", Malaysia's first trust fund for women.
</P>
<P>
"We should try to mobilize this wealth, assets and properties
that we have because we need the capital," he said.
</P>
<P>
The country's wealth has been eroded by half since the Asian
financial turmoil hit the economy last July and it was time for
people to mobilize their wealth, he said.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the 52 percent decline in the value of the local
currency -- the ringgit to "rogue speculators."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said these currency traders had gained a lot by
selling currencies without thinking about the sufferings of the
people in countries whose currencies they had targeted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
