<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Wheat production Exceeds Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has reaped 1.75 million
tons of wheat this year, 100,000 tons more than the planned target
for the year, an English daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Observer attributed the better production of
wheat to a long cold spell in the months of December and January
and a larger wheat sowing acreage with a total of 800,000 hectares
of farmland, as well as improved irrigation this year.
</P>
<P>
The government is planning to bring one million hectares of
land under wheat cultivation which would yield approximately two
million tons of wheat next year, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
