<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Launches First Women's Trust Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Tuesday launched its
first trust fund for women to help enhance their role in society
through greater participation in the nation's economic life.
</P>
<P>
The fund, known as Amanah Saham Wanita or Asnita in short
(Women's Trust Fund), and was initiated by the ruling Barisan
Nasional (National Front) Wanita (women) Movement, was launched by
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad who is also chairman of the
Barisan Nasional.
</P>
<P>
Asnita, approved by the Securities Commission (SC) on April 23,
comprises 400 million units at an initial offer price of 50 sen
(about 13.5 U.S. cents) per unit during the 21-day initial offer
period from May 4 to 24, and an investor needs a minimum of 200
units to start the investment.
</P>
<P>
Additional investment can be made at the prevailing market
price based on the net asset value of the unit.
</P>
<P>
Asnita investors enjoy facilities such as direct pay-deduction
through standing orders to banks or employers, joint holding
accounts for spouse and trust account on behalf of children or
other named beneficiaries.
</P>
<P>
Although it is specially designed for women, Asnita is open to
Malaysian citizens aged 18 and above, foreign citizens as well as
corporations, institutions and government bodies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
