<HEADLINE> China Vital in Regional, Global Stability: Austrian Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 4 (Xinhua) -- With its ever growing importance in
the world, China is playing a more vital role in maintaining
regional and global stability, Austrian Defense Minister Werner
Fasslabend told a visiting high-ranking Chinese military official
Monday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here with the Chief of the General Staff for the
Chinese People's Liberation Army Fu Quanyou, Fasslabend called for
joint efforts by the two countries to work for peace and stability
in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said Fu's visit, his first to Austria, is highly significant
and described it as "a new milestone" in military relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian defense minister said his country, which is
scheduled to serve as the rotating presidency of the European
Union in two months, is closely watching developments in China.
</P>
<P>
He said there exists no fundamental conflicts of interest and
there are wide-ranging areas available for cooperation between
Austria and China, and between Europe and China.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of China's Central Military Commission, said
relations between the armed forces of the two countries are being
strengthened through the sound and smooth progress of bilateral
ties and increased high-level dialogues.
</P>
<P>
He said his visit is intended to further mutual understanding
and confidence and to promote friendship and cooperation between
the two nations.
</P>
<P>
China hopes to develop multi-level cooperation with Austria in
different fields and to join efforts with Austria to build a
long-term and stable friendly relation oriented towards the 21st
century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Briefing his host on the Chinese government's policy on Taiwan,
Fu stressed adherence to President Jiang Zemin's eight-point
proposals on developing relations between the two sides across the
Taiwan Straits and pushing for the peaceful reunification of the
nation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China does not renounce the use of force, which is
not directed at compatriots in Taiwan, but at foreign interference
with China's reunification, and outside attempts to seek
"independence" for Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Fasslabend praised China for its independent foreign policy of
peace, and for its efforts to promote good-neighborly friendship,
peace, stability and development in neighboring countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
