<HEADLINE> Italian President to Visit Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro
leaves Tuesday for a three-day state visit to Sweden to exchange
views with Swedish leaders on the prospects and risks inherent in
the single European currency.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to hold talks with Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf
and Prime Minister Goran Persson and make a speech in the Swedish
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Like the United Kingdom, Sweden has chosen not to be a member
of the euro states in the first wave, even though its economy had
easily fallen within the parameters laid down by the Maastricht
Treaty.
</P>
<P>
With his trip to Sweden, Scalfaro will have been to all of the
European Union countries since the start of his seven-year
presidential term. 
</P>
