<HEADLINE> ASEAN Head Expects Good Hanoi Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Rodolfo Severino, secretary-general
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), said on
Monday the coming sixth ASEAN summit in Hanoi will be successful.
</P>
<P>
Severino, who is on an official visit to Vietnam, made the
remark during a meeting with Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai, the Vietnam News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He then briefed Phan on main points of the "Hanoi plan of
action" and other documents to be submitted to the ASEAN summit in
December.
</P>
<P>
Phan expressed the hope that cooperative ties between Vietnam
and ASEAN would be further enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He said the Hanoi summit should specify its plan of action in
line with the spirit of the "ASEAN vision 2020" approved at the
second informal ASEAN summit in Kuala Lumpur late last year.
</P>
<P>
The association should find its own way to overcome the current
financial crisis and continue to achieve high economic growth,
Phan said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that Cambodia would be considered
for admittance as the 10th member of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam joined ASEAN in July 1995. The other eight member
states are Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, Laos, the
Philippines, Singapore and Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
