</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Blue-chip stocks on Wall Street barely set a new
high Monday as a late wave of selling wiped out most of the day's
gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 45.59 points to 9,192.66,
down from a 115-point gain, but still enough to top April 21's
record close of 9,184.94. (New York-Stocks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Major stock markets in Europe extended last Friday's
rally and ended sharply higher Monday, boosted by benign
U.S. economic data and a European Union summit heralding the
participation of 11 countries in the European single currency next
year.
</P>
<P>
The London market was closed Monday for the May bank holiday
and will reopen Tuesday. The FTSE-100 index of leading shares
closed up 82 points or 1.83 percent at 6,010.3 last
Friday. (Europe-Stocks)
