<HEADLINE> No Fixed Timetable for Sweden to Join EMU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Finance Minister Erik
Asbrink clarified on Monday that there is no fixed timetable for
Sweden to join European Economic and Monetary Union (EMU).
</P>
<P>
The minister said this after comments he made over the weekend
were interpreted as meaning that Sweden could join the EMU before
the introduction of euro.
</P>
<P>
Asbrink said there was no debate in Sweden about linking the
Swedish currency crown to European Exchange Rate Mechanism (ERM).
</P>
<P>
"But exactly how this criteria will be interpreted remains to
be seen," he said.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister added that he was "rather confident" that
the Swedish crown would continue to do well, even outside the
EMU. 
</P>
