<HEADLINE> Prices in Guangdong Province Continue to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Commodity prices in south China's
Guangdong Province continued to fall during the first quarter of
the year, with the retail price index and the consumer price index
dropping 1.9 percent and 0.7 percent respectively on the 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
Prices for major commodities such as meet, poultry, eggs,
aquatic products, fruit and grain fell by a wide margin. However,
prices for vegetable remained stable due to climatic influences.
</P>
<P>
Prices for durable consumer goods all fell, while charges for
medical treatment and related services grew by 7.9 percent
compared to last year's same period. 
</P>
