<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Rising in Suzhou Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Suzhou Industrial Park, a joint
project of the Chinese and Singapore governments in east China's
Jiangsu Province, has so far introduced 3.66 billion U.S. dollars
of overseas investment and ranks fourth among the country's
37 development zones in terms of the use of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
Of the existing 117 overseas-funded enterprises in the park, 35
have so far added 1.17 billion U.S. dollars of investment, nearly
74 million U.S. dollars of which were added during the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Advanced Micro Devices Inc., one of the top five semiconductor
firms in the United States, has increased its investment in the
park to 108 million U.S. dollars from 36 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Eisai (Suzhou) Pharmaceuticals Co. Ltd. has become the
fourth biggest production base of the renowned Japanese drug
company.
</P>
<P>
In the zone, 31 overseas-funded industrial project are now
under construction.
</P>
<P>
More than 4.6 billion yuan has been spent on infrastructure
construction in the past three years in the park, which is
expected to turn into a world-level comprehensive industrial zone
after 10 to 15 years of construction work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
