<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Court Clears Slavkov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Olympic Committee (BOC)
chairman Ivan Slavkov has been cleared by the country's Supreme
Court of Appeals of misappropriation charges.
</P>
<P>
The supreme court had rejected an appeal by the chief
prosecutor against a decision by the Sofia City Court.
</P>
<P>
The Sofia court acquitted Slavkov of charges that he used money
from BOC to fund his son's trips abroad and to entertain foreign
visitors.
</P>
<P>
Because of the charges, he had been banned from travelling
abroad as the Balkan country's International Olympic Committee
member and barred from attending the 1992 Summer Games in
Barcelona and 1994 Winter Olympics in Lillehamer, Norway. 
