<HEADLINE> Euro-African Zone Davis Cup Group IV Matches Kicks Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The five-nation Group IV of the
Euro-African zone of the Davis Cup kicked off Monday in Ndola,
Zambia's important industrial city located 330 kilometers north of
the capital.
</P>
<P>
Zambian vice-president Criston Tembo officiated the opening of
the competition in the morning, Dr. John Bahana, an organiser from
the Zamiban Tennis Association, told Xinhua from Ndola Tennis Club
in a telephone interview.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 20 players from Zambia, Ethiopia, Algeria, Iceland
and Liechtenstein will compete in the event which concludes
Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
