<HEADLINE> Greece to Introduce First Electrically-Powered Trains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Greece will introduce this Autumn its
first electrically-powered trains on its route from the northern
Greek city of Thessaloniki to Eidomeni, near the border with the
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The electricity supply installations have been completed on the
Thessaloniki-Eidomeni section, and the state-run Greek Railways
Organization (OSE) has begun personnel training, the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The OSE currently continues its studies on the installations of
an electrical network on the Athens-Thessaloniki route.  
</P>
</TEXT>
