<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP Helps Vietnam Fight Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Fund (UNDP) is contributing 2.4 million U.S. dollars
to Vietnam's poverty-eradication efforts, the UNDP said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The income-boosting program will benefit 30,000 impoverished
households in the mountainous Ha Giang province, the UNDP said in
a press release.
</P>
<P>
The program aims at improving basic social services and
food-production techniques and supporting community-based
development initiatives.
</P>
<P>
More than one-third of the families in Ha Giang province live
in poverty, according to the UNDP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
