<HEADLINE> Dow Barely Beats Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip stocks on Wall Street
barely set a new high Monday as a late wave of selling wiped out
most of the day's gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 45.59 points to 9,192.66,
down from a 115-point gain, but still enough to top April 21's
record close of 9,184.94.
</P>
<P>
Several broad-market indexes flirted with new highs before
fading into the close as the rally that began on Thursday lost its
momentum.
</P>
<P>
Stocks opened the day strong, adding their gains from Thursday
and Friday, when a series of new economic data reinforced the
long-standing belief of steady, noninflationary growth.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outpaced decliners by a small margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 550.66 million
shares as against 571.84 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 1.07 to 1,122.07, and the NYSE
composite index rose 0.82 to 582.73.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 3.76 to 1,877.20.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.52 to
485.26, while the American Stock Exchange composite index fell
1.06 to 748.80.  
</P>
</TEXT>
